  "text": "One challenging aspect of multicentric radiomic studies is the sensitivity of radiomic features with respect to the variability of scanner models, acquisition protocols and reconstruction algorithms and parameters. Recently, a radiomic model exploiting FDG positron emission tomography (PET) and MRI apparent coefficient diffusion (ADC) map to predict outcome in LACC was validated in a multicentric context (3 different centers), thanks to the use of the ComBat harmonization technique [CITATION_1] . In that respect, the study of Sun, et al. showed that z-score normalization [CITATION_2] of each slice of the MR images intensities as well as of the features of each patient could allow good performance, despite different 3.0-T and 1.5-T MRI scanner models from several different vendors across the 8 centres.",
